agentScalarEntry.name: agentScalarEntry
agentScalarEntry.description: A component entry containing objects for a particular component.

paIdentify.name: paIdentify
paIdentify.description: Flash the READY light on the SAN Data Gateway front panel. A non-zero value turns the LED on for the specified number of seconds. Zero turns LED off.

paReboot.name: paReboot
paReboot.description: Writing a reboot(2) value here causes immediate reboot.

paHealthCheckValue.name: paHealthCheckValue
paHealthCheckValue.description: Value in percent of health check tests passed.

paHealthCheckLevel.name: paHealthCheckLevel
paHealthCheckLevel.description: Scrutiny level of health check function.

paEvRptLevel.name: paEvRptLevel
paEvRptLevel.description: Used when retrieving Event Log. Events with log level greater than paEvRptLevel are not retrieved.

paEventLogLevels.name: paEventLogLevels
paEventLogLevels.description: Each of 255 event types has an 8-bit level used when reading log. Currently valid LogLevel range is 0-3.

paTrapThresholds.name: paTrapThresholds
paTrapThresholds.description: Each of 255 event types has an 8-bit threshold. When the number of events exceeds the Trap Threshold, a trap is generated and sent to all parties listed in the trap destination table (also under SNMP control) . Threshold 0 means Never Threshold 1 means Always Threshold 2 - 255 means Number of events per 10 minute period

paBaudRate.name: paBaudRate
paBaudRate.description: Serial baud rate for SAN Gateway Service Port. Currently, the Agent does not support baud rate change: the rate is hard-coded to 19200 baud.

paLogSize.name: paLogSize
paLogSize.description: Number of records in entire event log. (Not just current records since boot.)

paCommand.name: paCommand
paCommand.description: Used for issuing command to SNMP agent.

paLogBoot.name: paLogBoot
paLogBoot.description: Absolute index of first log entry at boot.

paLogNCurrent.name: paLogNCurrent
paLogNCurrent.description: SNMP Get (read) returns number of records since boot subject to viewing level filtering. SNMP Set (write) copies this number of records since boot (subject to level filtering) into a buffer from which records are read. This mode of use is deprecated. The preferred way to get the event log since boot is to read paLogBoot, set paEvRptLevel and do a series of SNMP GetNext calls starting at instance paLogBoot until end of event log MIB table is reached.

paLogChronFirst.name: paLogChronFirst
paLogChronFirst.description: Used to request range of records from paLogChronFirst to paLogChronLast

paLogChronLast.name: paLogChronLast
paLogChronLast.description: Used to request range of records from paLogChronFirst to paLogChronLast

paLogScroll.name: paLogScroll
paLogScroll.description: Used to request previous/next range of records event log

paLogFilename.name: paLogFilename
paLogFilename.description: Used to save event log to a file.

paEnvironmentState.name: paEnvironmentState
paEnvironmentState.description: Temperature and Voltage Status of SAN Data Gateway: ********************************** (LSB) bit 0 Auxiliary Power bit 1 Main Power bit 2 Temperature Warning bit 3 Temperature Alarm

paGatewayFWRev.name: paGatewayFWRev
paGatewayFWRev.description: SAN Data Gateway Firmware Revision information.

paGatewayHWRev.name: paGatewayHWRev
paGatewayHWRev.description: SAN Data Gateway Hardware Revision information.

paServerVersion.name: paServerVersion
paServerVersion.description: Remote Management software writes Server version information here to customize SNMP Agent behavior.

paVPSEnabled.name: paVPSEnabled
paVPSEnabled.description: State of VPS Access Control enable.

paLicenseKey.name: paLicenseKey
paLicenseKey.description: Used to pass feature enabling license keys.

paThirdPartyCopyEnabled.name: paThirdPartyCopyEnabled
paThirdPartyCopyEnabled.description: State of Extended 3rd Party Copy enable. Enabled means that a valid license key has been entered for this feature.

paVPSStatus.name: paVPSStatus
paVPSStatus.description: State of Virtual Private SAN feature. bit 0 : active or inactive. bit 1 : licensed or not licensed. Bit 1 is redundant with MIB var paVPSEnabled. Writing 1 to bit 0 makes VPS active if licensed. Writing 0 to bit 0 makes VPS inactive if licensed.

paThirdPartyCopyStatus.name: paThirdPartyCopyStatus
paThirdPartyCopyStatus.description: State of Extended 3rd Party Copy feature. bit 0 : active or inactive. bit 1 : licensed or not licensed. Bit 1 is redundant with MIB var paThirdPartyCopyEnabled. Writing 1 to bit 0 makes Third Party Copy active if licensed. Writing 0 to bit 0 makes Third Party Copy inactive if licensed.

paSanDirectorEnabled.name: paSanDirectorEnabled
paSanDirectorEnabled.description: State of SAN Director Support for this device. To enable, user must write a valid license key to OID paLicenseKey or enter the license key from the service port.

paVPMStatus.name: paVPMStatus
paVPMStatus.description: State of Virtual Private Map feature. bit 0 : active or inactive. bit 1 : licensed or not licensed.

paSRSStatus.name: paSRSStatus
paSRSStatus.description: State of SAN Replication Services feature. bit 0 : active or inactive. bit 1 : licensed or not licensed.

paTrapSequenceNumber.name: paTrapSequenceNumber
paTrapSequenceNumber.description: Sequence number of last trap sent by this SNMP Agent.

paSysNodeNameMode.name: paSysNodeNameMode
paSysNodeNameMode.description: Algorithm used when computing Fibre Channel World Wide Node Name for each port. If the value is sameForEachPort(0), then the World Wide Node Name is the same for each port and computed based on the World Wide Node Name of the gateway. If the value is differentForEachPort(1), then the World Wide Node Name is different for each port, computed based on the World Wide Port Name for that port.

paGhostIOTimeToLive.name: paGhostIOTimeToLive
paGhostIOTimeToLive.description: The amount of time that commands can remain queued in the SNC before being considered stale and discarded. 0 : Never discard (ghost I/O disabled) 1 - 30 : TTL in ticks (60th of a second)

paEVPSEnabled.name: paEVPSEnabled
paEVPSEnabled.description: Bit 0: EVPS active if 1, inactive if 0 Bit 1: EVPS licensed if 1, unlicensed if 0

paMaxHostLun.name: paMaxHostLun
paMaxHostLun.description: The number of devices one host can see

paAMPStatus.name: paAMPStatus
paAMPStatus.description: Status of Automatic Multipath feature. bit 0 : active or inactive. bit 1 : licensed or not licensed.

paHPFStatus.name: paHPFStatus
paHPFStatus.description: Bit 0: HPF active if 1, inactive if 0 Bit 1: HPF licensed if 1, unlicensed if 0

paSoip2iRescan.name: paSoip2iRescan
paSoip2iRescan.description: Writing true(1) here causes SOIP2 initiator to rescan its bus.

paSoipiRescan.name: paSoipiRescan
paSoipiRescan.description: Writing true(1) here causes SOIP initiator to rescan its bus.

paFLBStatus.name: paFLBStatus
paFLBStatus.description: Status of Load Balancing feature. bit 0 : active or inactive. bit 1 : licensed or not licensed.

paSoip2iScanPeriod.name: paSoip2iScanPeriod
paSoip2iScanPeriod.description: SOIP2 Initiator Scan period in seconds. 0 will disable scan.

paCommandFlowLogEnabled.name: paCommandFlowLogEnabled
paCommandFlowLogEnabled.description: Returns TRUE iff Command Flow Logging is available. Returns FALSE otherwise.

paEventLog.name: paEventLog
paEventLog.description: Entry point for the Agent Event Log Table.

paProducer.name: paProducer
paProducer.description: Numeric identifier for this event's producer.

paEventClass.name: paEventClass
paEventClass.description: Numeric identifier for this event's class.

paSeq.name: paSeq
paSeq.description: Sequence number (relative record number) since boot.

pdDevices.name: pdDevices
pdDevices.description: Pathlight Physical Device Group *********************************** Each device attached to the Gateway has an entry here.

pdIdentify.name: pdIdentify
pdIdentify.description: Number of seconds to flash identifying LED. Write here to flash LED on device if supported by Gateway and device. Zero turns LED off.

pdInterfaceType.name: pdInterfaceType
pdInterfaceType.description: This device's type of communication interface.

pdCtlrIndex.name: pdCtlrIndex
pdCtlrIndex.description: Index of this device's controller in the Controllers MIB table and type-specific controller tables

pdReset.name: pdReset
pdReset.description: Generic device reset if supported. Write reset(1) here to reset device if supported by Gateway firmware and device.

pdStatusBits.name: pdStatusBits
pdStatusBits.description: Device status bits as per SCSI spec.

pdTargetLun.name: pdTargetLun
pdTargetLun.description: This target device's Logical Unit Number as seen from attached host.

pdIpAddress.name: pdIpAddress
pdIpAddress.description: This target device's IP Address if applicable. In case of SAN Gateway or Router, this information is used to allow arbitrary drill-down capability.

pcControllers.name: pcControllers
pcControllers.description: Pathlight Controller Group ******************************* All controllers installed in the SAN Data Gateway have an entry here AND a parallel entry in the controller-type specific table (Fibre Channnel, SSA, or SCSI).

pcVendorId.name: pcVendorId
pcVendorId.description: Integer vendor ID for this controller.

pcProductId.name: pcProductId
pcProductId.description: Vendor's integer ID for this controller.

pcRevision.name: pcRevision
pcRevision.description: Revision information for this controller. See also pcHWRev and pcFWRev.

pcSubVendor.name: pcSubVendor
pcSubVendor.description: Integer sub-vendor ID for this controller.

pcSubProduct.name: pcSubProduct
pcSubProduct.description: Vendor's integer sub-product ID for this controller.

pcMaxBurst.name: pcMaxBurst
pcMaxBurst.description: Maximum burst transfer rate in MBytes/second

pcIdentify.name: pcIdentify
pcIdentify.description: Reserved for flashing identifying LED on device.

pcPCIBus.name: pcPCIBus
pcPCIBus.description: PCI Bus number in SAN Data Gateway for this controller.

pcPCIDev.name: pcPCIDev
pcPCIDev.description: PCI device number in SAN Data Gateway for this controller.

pcPCIFunc.name: pcPCIFunc
pcPCIFunc.description: PCI Function number in SAN Data Gateway for this contoller.

pcReset.name: pcReset
pcReset.description: Generic controller reset variable. Not supported for all controller types.

pcRescan.name: pcRescan
pcRescan.description: Writing true(1) here causes controller to rescan its bus if rescan is supported for this controller type.

pcPCISlot.name: pcPCISlot
pcPCISlot.description: Location of Channel Card on PCI bus

pcPMCSlot.name: pcPMCSlot
pcPMCSlot.description: Location of Card: PMC 1, 2 or 3. 0=> Not a PMC card

pcPCIClass.name: pcPCIClass
pcPCIClass.description: Device class code as per PCI specification.

pcSplitMode.name: pcSplitMode
pcSplitMode.description: Enable/Disable Split Mode for this controller.

pcChannelMask.name: pcChannelMask
pcChannelMask.description: Specifies access permissions for this initiator in bits 0 through 18 ************************************************* -* SCSI Channels *- Bit 0 => Is access DISALLOWED to SCSI channel 1 ? Bit 1 => Is access DISALLOWED to SCSI channel 2 ? Bit 2 => Is access DISALLOWED to SCSI channel 3 ? Bit 3 => Is access DISALLOWED to SCSI channel 4 ? -* Ultra SCSI Channels *- Bit 4 => Is access DISALLOWED to Ultra SCSI channel 1 ? Bit 5 => Is access DISALLOWED to Ultra SCSI channel 2 ? Bit 6 => Is access DISALLOWED to Ultra SCSI channel 3 ? Bit 7 => Is access DISALLOWED to Ultra SCSI channel 4 ? Bit 8 => Is access DISALLOWED to Ultra SCSI channel 5 ? Bit 9 => Is access DISALLOWED to Ultra SCSI channel 6 ? -* Fibre Channel *- Bit 10 => Is access DISALLOWED to Fibre Channel 1 ? Bit 11 => Is access DISALLOWED to Fibre Channel 2 ? Bit 12 => Is access DISALLOWED to Fibre Channel 3 ? Bit 13 => Is access DISALLOWED to Fibre Channel 4 ? Bit 14 => Is access DISALLOWED to Fibre Channel 5 ? Bit 15 => Is access DISALLOWED to Fibre Channel 6 ? -* SSA Channels *- Bit 16 => Is access DISALLOWED to SSA channel 1 ? Bit 17 => Is access DISALLOWED to SSA Channel 2 ? Bit 18 => Is access DISALLOWED to SSA Channel 3 ?

pcPortHostType.name: pcPortHostType
pcPortHostType.description: Host type for this port. Used if VPS is not enabled.

pcFCCtlrs.name: pcFCCtlrs
pcFCCtlrs.description: Entry point for Fibre Channel Controller Device Group ****************************************************** This table parallels the Controller Table: a Fibre Channel controller with pcIndex N in the controller table appears here as index N as well, and in general there are rows in this table which are empty.

fcStatus.name: fcStatus
fcStatus.description: Status of the Fibre Channel Controller

fcMaxSpeed.name: fcMaxSpeed
fcMaxSpeed.description: Maximum Transfer Speed in MBytes per second.

fcWWID.name: fcWWID
fcWWID.description: World Wide Identifier for this Fibre Channel Controller.

fcFWRev.name: fcFWRev
fcFWRev.description: Firmware revision number/identifier for this Fibre Channel Controller.

fcHWRev.name: fcHWRev
fcHWRev.description: Hardware revision number/identifier for this Fibre Channel Controller.

fcMedia.name: fcMedia
fcMedia.description: Media type for this Fibre Channel Controller

fcSerialNumber.name: fcSerialNumber
fcSerialNumber.description: Serial Number for this Fibre Channel Controller.

fcLoopIDMode.name: fcLoopIDMode
fcLoopIDMode.description: Fibre Channel Loop ID mode (soft or hard)

fcConnectionOptions.name: fcConnectionOptions
fcConnectionOptions.description: Connection options for ISP2200 FC chip. Values 4 - 8 are reserved.

fcCtlrChipType.name: fcCtlrChipType
fcCtlrChipType.description: Type of Fibre Channel controller chip. Valid types are 2100 , 2200 for QLogic ISP2100 and ISP2200 chips.

fcTapeFeature.name: fcTapeFeature
fcTapeFeature.description: Status of Fibre Channel Tape Specification support. true means this controller supports FC Tape false means this controller does not support FC Tape

fcHardID.name: fcHardID
fcHardID.description: Fibre Channel Hard ID, the preferred loop ID for this controller. Even if the controller is in Hard Loop ID mode, the actual loop ID is not guaranteed to be fcHardID.

fcLossSyncCount.name: fcLossSyncCount
fcLossSyncCount.description: Fibre Channel Loss of Sync Count

fcLossSignalCount.name: fcLossSignalCount
fcLossSignalCount.description: Fibre Channel Loss of Signal Count

fcProtocolErrorCount.name: fcProtocolErrorCount
fcProtocolErrorCount.description: Fibre Channel Primitive Sequence Protocol Error Count

fcInvalidTxWordCount.name: fcInvalidTxWordCount
fcInvalidTxWordCount.description: Fibre Channel Invalid Transmission Word Count

fcWWNodeName.name: fcWWNodeName
fcWWNodeName.description: The World Wide Node Name for this Fibre Channel Controller. The Node Name for this port may computer strictly on the World Wide Node Name for the gateway, or on a per port basis which uses the World Wide Port Name (fcWWID), thus giving each port a different Node Name. See paSysNodeNameMode to get or set which algorithm is in use.

fcPortID.name: fcPortID
fcPortID.description: Fibre Channel Port Identifier 24 bit quantity which uniquely identifies the port within the loop or fabric.

pcSSACtlrs.name: pcSSACtlrs
pcSSACtlrs.description: Entry point for SSA Controller Device Group **************************************************** This table parallels the Controller Table: an SSA controller with pcIndex N in the controller table appears here as row index N as well, and in general there are rows in this table which are empty.

ssaStatus1.name: ssaStatus1
ssaStatus1.description: Status on port 1 of dual port SSA card

ssaStatus2.name: ssaStatus2
ssaStatus2.description: Status on port 2 of dual port SSA card

ssaSpeed.name: ssaSpeed
ssaSpeed.description: SSA transfer speed 80 Mbytes/second or 160 MBytes/second

ssaUID.name: ssaUID
ssaUID.description: Universal Identifier for this SSA Controller.

ssaFWRev.name: ssaFWRev
ssaFWRev.description: Firmware revision number/identifier for this SSA controller.

ssaHWRev.name: ssaHWRev
ssaHWRev.description: Hardware revision number/identifier for this SSA controller.

ssaMasterPriority.name: ssaMasterPriority
ssaMasterPriority.description: The SSA Master Priority of an SSA node is a number from 0 to 7. SSA initiators elect a master based on this priority. If more than one SSA node has the same priority then the node with the highest UID is elected. Pathlight SSA host adapters default to a Master Priority of 4. SAN Gateway SSA Target adapters default to a priority of 5 to ensure that the Gateway node will be master in a multi-initiator loop. This value should never be set to 7 because this is the priority used to guarantee mastership to a node that is entering Service Mode.

ssaSATAQuota.name: ssaSATAQuota
ssaSATAQuota.description: The SSA SAT Quota A parameter is an 8 bit number that determines 'the maximum number of frames which can be originated from this port before the port is SATisfied and forwards the SAT character. A value of zero means that no SATs are forwarded or issued from this port.'

ssaSATBQuota.name: ssaSATBQuota
ssaSATBQuota.description: The SSA SAT Quota B parameter is an 8 bit number that determines 'the maximum number of frames which this port can originate without forwarding a SAT character. A value of zero means that an infinite number of frames can be sent without being subject to SAT pacing.'

pcSCSICtlrs.name: pcSCSICtlrs
pcSCSICtlrs.description: Entry point for SCSI Controller Device Group **************************************************** This table parallels the Controller Table: a SCSI controller with pcIndex N in the controller table appears here as row index N as well, and in general there are rows in this table which are empty.

scsiRole.name: scsiRole
scsiRole.description: Is this a Target or an Initiator ?

scsiMaxSpeed.name: scsiMaxSpeed
scsiMaxSpeed.description: Maximum Speed of this SCSI Channel.

scsiTerm.name: scsiTerm
scsiTerm.description: State of internal SCSI bus terminations, if any.

scsiMaxIds.name: scsiMaxIds
scsiMaxIds.description: Maximum Number of IDs for this SCSI controller.

scsiMaxLuns.name: scsiMaxLuns
scsiMaxLuns.description: Maximum Number of LUNs for this SCSI controller.

scsiHWRev.name: scsiHWRev
scsiHWRev.description: Hardware revision for this SCSI controller.

scsiFWRev.name: scsiFWRev
scsiFWRev.description: Firmware revision for this SCSI controller.

scsiResetOnPowerUp.name: scsiResetOnPowerUp
scsiResetOnPowerUp.description: Enables/Disables SCSI bus reset upon Gateway power-up for this SCSI controller.

scsiMultiInitEnabled.name: scsiMultiInitEnabled
scsiMultiInitEnabled.description: Enables/Disables multi-initiator support on for this SCSI controller.

scsiAlternateHostId.name: scsiAlternateHostId
scsiAlternateHostId.description: Alternate Host ID for this SCSI controller. -1 means use automatic.

scsiTargetEnabled.name: scsiTargetEnabled
scsiTargetEnabled.description: Indicates target ScsiRole support for this SCSI controller.

pnTrapDest.name: pnTrapDest
pnTrapDest.description: Trap destination Group Table ****************************************** A list of IP addresses to which SNMP Traps are sent in parallel using UDP Port 162.

pnIPAddr.name: pnIPAddr
pnIPAddr.description: IP Address of destination entity to which traps are sent.

pnUdpPort.name: pnUdpPort
pnUdpPort.description: UDP Port on which traps are sent to this entity.

pnTrapStyle.name: pnTrapStyle
pnTrapStyle.description: Style to be used when building a trap PDU to be sent to this entity. A value of proprietary(1) selects the proprietary format used by the Pathlight SAN Director management application. A value of rfc1215(2) selects the format as described in the RFC 1215 TRAP-TYPE objects included in this MIB document. The default is proprietary(1).

pnTrapBroadcastMode.name: pnTrapBroadcastMode
pnTrapBroadcastMode.description: Used to Enable/Disable the broadcasting of traps.

hostCommandEntry.name: hostCommandEntry
hostCommandEntry.description: An object for issuing host-related commands to the SNC.

hostCommand.name: hostCommand
hostCommand.description: Used to issue commands to VPS control software. Possible commands are: commitChanges: commits any pending LUN Mapping changes to persistent memory.

hostInitiator.name: hostInitiator
hostInitiator.description: Attached Host Group Table *************************** List of attached hosts and pertinent information.

hostWWName.name: hostWWName
hostWWName.description: World Wide name of this Initiator.

hostType.name: hostType
hostType.description: Operating System and other host environment information.

hostSANConnection.name: hostSANConnection
hostSANConnection.description: SAN Connection (1-6) to which this host is connected.

hostITLData.name: hostITLData
hostITLData.description: ITL Access Control data for this host. 256 possible LUNs with one Byte of data per LUN.

hostIPAddr.name: hostIPAddr
hostIPAddr.description: IP Address of this host. Host is not required to have an IP address.

hostLunType.name: hostLunType
hostLunType.description: The type of this host for EVPS. 8-bit, 16-bit, or volume set

hostLunMap.name: hostLunMap
hostLunMap.description: EVPS Map data. 256 possible LUNs with two Bytes of data for each lun

hostInbandAccess.name: hostInbandAccess
hostInbandAccess.description: The in-band access level of the host

scsiMapCommandEntry.name: scsiMapCommandEntry
scsiMapCommandEntry.description: An object for issuing VPM-related commands to the SNC.

scsiMapCommand.name: scsiMapCommand
scsiMapCommand.description: Used to issue commands to SCSI Channel map (VPM) routines.

scsiChannelMap.name: scsiChannelMap
scsiChannelMap.description: SCSI Channel Device Map Table ****************************** List of devices presented to SCSI attached initiator. The initiator sees a series of (Target ID , LUN ) SCSI targets which are mapped to a logical device identified by a Pathlight assigned LUN.

scsiMapRowStatus.name: scsiMapRowStatus
scsiMapRowStatus.description: Specifies the state of the row.

scsiMapPort.name: scsiMapPort
scsiMapPort.description: SCSI port (bus) number for this entry (1 thru 10).

scsiMapTid.name: scsiMapTid
scsiMapTid.description: SCSI Target ID for this entry.

scsiMapAssignedLun.name: scsiMapAssignedLun
scsiMapAssignedLun.description: Pathlight LUN assigned to this entry. This assigned LUN maps to some device connected to the Gateway/Router by some other means (FC, SSA, SCSI, ...).

scsiMapPdIndex.name: scsiMapPdIndex
scsiMapPdIndex.description: Index into Pathlight SANMgr MIB Device Table ( pd group ). The Device Table has more detailed information about attached devices.

deviceMapCommandEntry.name: deviceMapCommandEntry
deviceMapCommandEntry.description: An object for issuing VPM-related commands to the SNC.

deviceMapCommand.name: deviceMapCommand
deviceMapCommand.description: Used to issue commands to device map map routines.

deviceMapMultipathMode.name: deviceMapMultipathMode
deviceMapMultipathMode.description: Used to set the Multipath mode.

deviceMapRemoveDevice.name: deviceMapRemoveDevice
deviceMapRemoveDevice.description: Used to remove a device from the Device Map given its Device-Id. Warning: This command stops the IO for this device before removing

deviceLoadBalancingMode.name: deviceLoadBalancingMode
deviceLoadBalancingMode.description: Used to set the Load Balancing Mode.

dmDeviceMap.name: dmDeviceMap
dmDeviceMap.description: Device Map Group *********************************** Each device attached to the Gateway has an entry here. Historical data of devices not presently connected may also appear here.

dmRowStatus.name: dmRowStatus
dmRowStatus.description: Row Control Object for this row

dmAssignedLun.name: dmAssignedLun
dmAssignedLun.description: Logical Unit Number assigned to this attached device. Range is 0 thru 255.

dmType.name: dmType
dmType.description: Type of device (FC, SCSI, SNA, SSA).

dmPort.name: dmPort
dmPort.description: SAN Gateway Port to which this device is connected. May be 1 thru 10 for SCSI, 1 thru 6 for Fibre Channel, 1 thru 3 for SSA.

dmTargetId.name: dmTargetId
dmTargetId.description: The Target ID of the attached target device. This is the actual target ID of the device, not fabricated by the Gateway or Router.

dmTargetLun.name: dmTargetLun
dmTargetLun.description: The Logical Unit Number of the attached target device. This is the actual LUN of the device, not fabricated by the Gateway or Router.

dmUid.name: dmUid
dmUid.description: A universally unique identifier for this target device.

dmPath.name: dmPath
dmPath.description: The Multipath Mode of the device. The mode can only be single(0), manual(1), or auto(1).

dmSerialNum.name: dmSerialNum
dmSerialNum.description: The Serial Number of the device.

srsDevTable.name: srsDevTable
srsDevTable.description: Entry point for SAN Replication Service Device Group ***************************************************** Each SAN Replication Service Device has an entry in this table

srsDevId.name: srsDevId
srsDevId.description: Device ID for this SRS Device.

srsDevState.name: srsDevState
srsDevState.description: State of this LUN Replicated Device.

srsDevCommand.name: srsDevCommand
srsDevCommand.description: Used to invoke SAN Replication Services API commands. Parameters may be passed in the same SNMP Set varbind list with the srsDevCommand as the last varbind. ********************************************* create(1) - Creates a new SRS Device delete(2) - Deletes an existing SRS Device

srsDevAssignedLun.name: srsDevAssignedLun
srsDevAssignedLun.description: Assigned LUN of the SAN Replication Service Device's Primary.

srsDevMemberCount.name: srsDevMemberCount
srsDevMemberCount.description: Number of members of this LUN Replicated Device.

srsDevFlags.name: srsDevFlags
srsDevFlags.description: SCSI device flags for this SAN Replication Service Device.

srsDevSizeInBlocks.name: srsDevSizeInBlocks
srsDevSizeInBlocks.description: Size in blocks of this SAN Replication Services Device.

srsDevPrimary.name: srsDevPrimary
srsDevPrimary.description: The Assigned LUN of this SRS Device's Primary.

srsMemTable.name: srsMemTable
srsMemTable.description: Entry point for SAN Replication Services Member Group ***************************************************** This table lists the Members of each SRS Device.

srsMemDeviceId.name: srsMemDeviceId
srsMemDeviceId.description: Device ID of the SAN Replication Services Device to which this member belongs.

srsMemId.name: srsMemId
srsMemId.description: Member ID (index) of this member device.

srsMemState.name: srsMemState
srsMemState.description: State of this SAN Replication Services Device Member.

srsMemCommand.name: srsMemCommand
srsMemCommand.description: Used to invoke SAN Replication Services API methods. Parameters may be passed in the same SNMP Set varbind list with the lrmCommand as the last varbind.

srsMemType.name: srsMemType
srsMemType.description: Is this device a primary or secondary member.

srsMemSyncPoint.name: srsMemSyncPoint
srsMemSyncPoint.description: Number of blocks synchronized so far. Used for monitoring synchronization.

srsMemAssignedLun.name: srsMemAssignedLun
srsMemAssignedLun.description: Assigned LUN for this SRS Member.

envDataTable.name: envDataTable
envDataTable.description: Entry point for Environmental Data Group ***************************************************** This table lists the attributes of each environmental data.

envNominalLo.name: envNominalLo
envNominalLo.description: Minimum value for Nominal status Warning state occurs if the current value is less than this

envNominalHi.name: envNominalHi
envNominalHi.description: Maximum Value for Nominal status Warning state occurs if the current value is greater than this.

envWarningLo.name: envWarningLo
envWarningLo.description: Minimum value for Warning status Alarm state occurs if the current value is less than this

envWarningHi.name: envWarningHi
envWarningHi.description: Maximum Value for Warning status Alarm state occurs if the current value is greater than this.

envCurStatus.name: envCurStatus
envCurStatus.description: Current Status: Nominal, Warning, or Alarm.

fcHPFPortMappings.name: fcHPFPortMappings
fcHPFPortMappings.description: FC Host Port Failover Mapping *********************************** This table consists of port mappings for the FC Host Port Failover

fcHPFMapEntry.name: fcHPFMapEntry
fcHPFMapEntry.description: SNMP table for FC Host Port Failover Mappings

fcHPFMapRowStatus.name: fcHPFMapRowStatus
fcHPFMapRowStatus.description: Row Control Object for this row

fcHPFMapVirtualPort.name: fcHPFMapVirtualPort
fcHPFMapVirtualPort.description: The virtual port index. Depends on the configuration. Usaually same as phys port index, but 0 if not configured

fcHPFMapPrimaryPort.name: fcHPFMapPrimaryPort
fcHPFMapPrimaryPort.description: The physical port index that acts as the default standby

fcHPFMapStandbyList.name: fcHPFMapStandbyList
fcHPFMapStandbyList.description: The comma seperated list of ports that are configured as standbys for the virtual port, excluding the primary port.

fcHPFMapActivePort.name: fcHPFMapActivePort
fcHPFMapActivePort.description: The physical port thats active on this virtual port

fcHPFPhysicalPorts.name: fcHPFPhysicalPorts
